In February 2009, the President of the United States met with approximately 40 family members of the victims of the September 11th attacks and the attack on the USS Cole. The President thanked them for speaking out about these tragic events and expressed his desire for an ongoing dialogue. He emphasized his responsibility to keep the American people safe and explained why he believed closing Guantanamo would enhance national security and ensure justice for those responsible. The President engaged in a dialogue with the families, answering questions and promising an ongoing forum for discussion. The conversation covered a wide range of views and was described as substantive and emotional.